---
import "../styles/global.css";
import ThemeToggle from "../components/ThemeToggle.astro";
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width" />
    <title>FAQ — ROM Hacks</title>
    <link rel="icon" href="data:image/svg+xml,<svg xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'><text y='32' font-size='32'>🕹️</text></svg>" />
    <meta name="description" content="Frequently asked questions about ROM hacks and how to use the browser-based patcher and MAME Lua plugin generator." />
    <script is:inline>
      const t = localStorage.getItem("theme");
      if (t === "light" || t === "dark")
        document.documentElement.dataset.theme = t;
    </script>
  </head>
  <body>
    <a class="skip-link" href="#main-content">Skip to content</a>
    <header>
      <div class="header-row">
        <h1>Frequently Asked Questions</h1>
        <ThemeToggle />
      </div>
      <p class="muted">Frequently asked questions about ROM hacks and how to use this site.</p>
      <a href="/" class="back-link">← Back to ROM Hacks</a>
    </header>

    <main id="main-content">
      <nav class="toc" aria-label="Table of contents">
        <ol>
          <li><a href="#what-is-a-rom-hack">What is a ROM hack?</a></li>
          <li><a href="#which-romset">Which ROM set is supported?</a></li>
          <li><a href="#how-to-patch">How do I patch a ROM?</a></li>
          <li><a href="#run-patched-rom">How do I run a patched ROM in MAME?</a></li>
          <li><a href="#mame-plugin">How do I use hacks without patching the ROM?</a></li>
        </ol>
      </nav>

      <div class="faq">
        <section class="faq-item" id="what-is-a-rom-hack">
          <h2 class="faq-question">What is a ROM hack?</h2>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>
              A ROM hack is a modified version of a game's read-only memory
              (ROM) dump. Hobbyists and enthusiasts reverse-engineer the
              original binary and apply patches that change gameplay,
              difficulty, graphics, sounds, or other aspects of the game.
            </p>
            <p>
              For arcade games specifically, hacks typically target things like
              difficulty balancing, region-specific censorship removal, score or
              timer tweaks, or quality-of-life improvements that the original
              developers never shipped.
            </p>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="faq-item" id="which-romset">
          <h2 class="faq-question">Which ROM set is supported?</h2>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>
              This site targets the <strong>MAME non-merged ROM set</strong>. In
              a non-merged set every game ships as a self-contained ZIP that
              includes all the files it needs — parent and clone ROMs alike — so
              you don't need a separate parent archive to run a clone.
            </p>
            <p>
              Other ROM sets (merged, split) may work but are not guaranteed to.
              If the patcher reports a CRC mismatch, switch to a non-merged set.
            </p>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="faq-item" id="how-to-patch">
          <h2 class="faq-question">How do I patch a ROM?</h2>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>
              Find the game in the list and check the hacks you want to apply — each
              game shows a list of checkboxes, and you can toggle any combination of
              hacks. Then load your ROM using one of two methods:
            </p>
            <ul>
              <li>
                <strong>Drag and drop</strong> — drag your ROM ZIP onto the patch area.
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>File picker</strong> — click <em>Select ROM</em> and choose
                your ZIP file.
              </li>
            </ul>
            <p>
              In both cases, click the <em>Patch</em> button to generate and download
              the patched ZIP. Your original file is never modified.
            </p>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="faq-item" id="run-patched-rom">
          <h2 class="faq-question">How do I run a patched ROM in MAME?</h2>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>
              You must launch the patched ROM from the <strong
                >command line</strong
              >. MAME's built-in UI performs a CRC integrity check against its
              internal database and will refuse to start any ROM whose checksums
              don't match — which is exactly the case for a patched file.
            </p>
            <p>Place your patched ZIP in a folder of your choice, then run:</p>
            <pre><code>mame -rompath /path/to/your/roms &lt;romname&gt;</code></pre>
            <p>
              Replace <code>/path/to/your/roms</code> with the folder containing your
              patched ZIP and <code>&lt;romname&gt;</code> with the ZIP filename without
              the extension (e.g. <code>ffight</code>). The <code>-rompath</code
              > flag tells MAME where to look without touching your main ROM directory.
            </p>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="faq-item" id="mame-plugin">
          <h2 class="faq-question">
            How do I use hacks without patching the ROM?
          </h2>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>
              Hacks on this site are available as a <strong
                >MAME Lua plugin</strong
              >
              instead of a ROM patch. The plugin applies changes to the game's live
              memory at runtime, so your original ROM files are never modified and
              keep passing MAME's CRC check.
            </p>
            <p>To use a plugin:</p>
            <ol>
              <li>
                Click <em>Generate plugin</em> on the game's entry and download the
                <code>.zip</code> file.
              </li>
              <li>
                Extract it into MAME's <code>plugins/</code> folder so the structure
                looks like
                <code>plugins/&lt;plugin-name&gt;/plugin.json</code>.
              </li>
              <li>
                Enable plugins in MAME — either through the in-game menu (<kbd
                  >Tab</kbd
                > → Plugin Options) or by adding
                <code>-plugins -plugin &lt;plugin-name&gt;</code> to your command
                line.
              </li>
              <li>
                Launch the game normally. The plugin loads automatically and
                patches memory on the fly each time you play.
              </li>
            </ol>
            <p>
              The plugin approach is ideal when you want to keep your ROM set
              untouched or switch hacks on and off without managing multiple ROM
              files.
            </p>
          </div>
        </section>
      </div>

    </main>

    <footer class="page-footer">
      <a href="/">← Back to ROM Hacks</a>
      <a href="#top">↑ Back to top</a>
    </footer>
  </body>
</html>

<style>
  .back-link {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    display: inline-block;
    margin-top: 0.4rem;
  }

  .toc {
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 6px;
    background: var(--surface);
  }

  .toc ol {
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.35rem;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .toc li {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  .page-footer {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }

  .faq {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
  }

  .faq-item {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.6rem;
    padding: 1.5rem 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .faq-item:first-child {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .faq-question {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: none;
    letter-spacing: 0;
    color: var(--text);
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .faq-answer {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    font-size: 0.88rem;
    color: var(--text);
  }

  .faq-answer p {
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .faq-answer strong {
    color: var(--text);
  }

  .faq-answer pre {
    background: var(--bg);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 4px;
    padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
    overflow-x: auto;
  }

  .faq-answer code {
    font-family: inherit;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--ok);
  }

  .faq-answer pre code {
    color: var(--ok);
  }

  .faq-answer ul,
  .faq-answer ol {
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.4rem;
  }

  .faq-answer li {
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  kbd {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 0.1rem 0.4rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 3px;
    font-family: inherit;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    background: var(--bg);
    color: var(--text);
  }
</style>
